d helping a reviewer\n    41\tunderstand the change.\n    42\t\n    43\t## Core Question\n    44\t\n    45\tAgent Trail should answer:\n    46\t\n    47\t> What agent context helps me review this pull request?\n    48\t\n    49\tIt should not claim:\n    50\t\n    51\t> This agent session authored this pull request.\n    52\t\n    53\tThe language should stay evidence-based. Say that a session or turn is related\n    54\tto a pull request, branch, review, or ch\n[TRUNCATED]\n575\tThe big shape is clear enough now: Forge-hosted, public-repo v1, on-demand URL\n   576\tentry, generated snapshots, server-side repo cache, GitMeta fetch, and\n   577\t`but-agentlog` interpretation.\n   578\t\n   579\tThere are no major architecture blockers left.\n   580\t\n   581\tResolved for v1:\n   582\t\n   583\t- canonical PR target key: PR number as a `but-agentlog` review target,\n   584\t  normalized to `gitbutler-review:<number>`\n   585\t- metadata ref path: fetch `refs/meta/main` from the public repository resolved\n   586\t  from the PR URL\n   587\t- lookup inputs: search the PR/review target and the PR head branch\n   588\t- ranking: review-target matches rank above branch-only matches\n   589\t- snapshot identity: PR number plus metadata ref OID plus selected session/turn\n   590\t  keys\n   591\t- fork PRs: not supported in the initial version\n   592\t- public redaction: no extra public-web redaction layer beyond baseline\n   593\t  `but-agentlog` redaction\n   594\t\n   595\tDeferred until implementation:\n   596\t\n   597\t- exact projection payload returned from `but-agentlog` to Forge\n   598\t- exact dedupe behavior when a session matches both review and branch targets\n   599\t- refresh and invalidation behavior for cached snapshots\n   600\t- detailed no-data and weak-evidence page copy\n   601\t- initial UI wireframe and interaction details\n   602\t\n   603\t## Implementation Boundary\n   604\t\n   605\tKeep the primitive crate boring.\n   606\t\n   607\t`but-age